1
00:00:00,690 --> 00:00:02,470
Hey, I'm here to do some shopping.

2
00:00:03,380 --> 00:00:04,380
Wait...

3
00:00:04,520 --> 00:00:05,520
Huh?

4
00:00:05,820 --> 00:00:06,820
Wait...

5
00:00:07,180 --> 00:00:08,180
What?!

6
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:09,570
Touma's father?

7
00:00:10,870 --> 00:00:12,750
What is he doing here?

8
00:00:12,820 --> 00:00:14,210
He's the CEO of Whimsical...

9
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:15,830
and Sahashi-kun's father.

10
00:00:15,880 --> 00:00:18,060
- Huh?
- Sahashi's dad?

11
00:00:18,520 --> 00:00:20,300
They're nothing alike.

12
00:00:20,660 --> 00:00:21,790
That's a surprise.

13
00:00:23,650 --> 00:00:24,860
Good work today.

14
00:00:26,830 --> 00:00:27,830
Huh?

15
00:00:27,920 --> 00:00:29,320
Good work, sir.

16
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:31,220
Come on, let's go have some fun.

17
00:00:32,880 --> 00:00:34,630
- Right now?
- Yeah, where should we go?

18
00:00:34,950 --> 00:00:37,110
Where to, where to... Where's a good spot?

19
00:00:44,970 --> 00:00:46,170
Good work.

20
00:00:46,780 --> 00:00:48,100
Still working overtime?

21
00:00:49,150 --> 00:00:50,730
That makeup video I sent earlier...

22
00:00:50,950 --> 00:00:52,410
It just got rejected.

23
00:00:53,330 --> 00:00:54,770
They want me to redo it.

24
00:00:56,220 --> 00:00:57,870
I'm so busy.

25
00:00:59,180 --> 00:01:00,890
Is it okay if you don't spend time with Mamiya-kun?

26
00:01:01,350 --> 00:01:03,130
It'll be March before we know it.

27
00:01:04,020 --> 00:01:05,220
That's exactly why.

28
00:01:09,070 --> 00:01:10,770
Because I want us to be together in the future,

29
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,860
I want to come back as soon as possible.

30
00:01:16,130 --> 00:01:17,130
To make that happen,

31
00:01:18,290 --> 00:01:20,050
I have to focus on what I can do right now.

32
00:01:24,090 --> 00:01:25,600
It's for our future.

33
00:01:28,930 --> 00:01:30,130
I see.

34
00:01:36,370 --> 00:01:37,520
By the way,

35
00:01:37,770 --> 00:01:40,310
about that collaboration with Whimsical next month...

36
00:01:41,050 --> 00:01:42,050
I heard about it.

37
00:01:43,330 --> 00:01:46,170
That's your dad's company, right?

38
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:51,010
That has nothing to do with me.

39
00:01:52,270 --> 00:01:53,270
Which means,

40
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,220
you'll be seeing your brother again.

41
00:02:56,500 --> 00:03:00,900
"Cosmetic Playlover" Season 2
(Episode 9)

42
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:03,720
Wow.

43
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:05,930
It's been a while since I've been back in Tokyo.

44
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:08,660
Everything's changed so much.

45
00:03:08,990 --> 00:03:09,990
Is this Shibuya?

46
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:11,150
Yeah.

47
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,920
Hey, why are there so many foreigners?

48
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:17,510
Well, I wonder why...

49
00:03:18,530 --> 00:03:19,720
I have no idea!

50
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,050
It's just like New York.

51
00:03:21,050 --> 00:03:22,180
No, this is definitely Tokyo.

52
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:23,730
Hey, what's that? What's that?

53
00:03:24,530 --> 00:03:26,370
- That looks like fun.
- Ah... yeah...

54
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:27,570
That's hilarious.

55
00:03:28,310 --> 00:03:29,410
It's like they're singing.

56
00:03:31,110 --> 00:03:32,110
Ah...

57
00:03:34,530 --> 00:03:36,530
I can't believe this place is still here.

58
00:03:37,470 --> 00:03:38,710
I used to come here all the time.

59
00:03:39,330 --> 00:03:42,920
- It's nice that some things never change.
- Is it...

60
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:45,600
- Sorry to keep you waiting.
- Thanks!

61
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:47,570
Why am I so exhausted?

62
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,870
It feels like my energy is being sucked out of me.

63
00:03:58,470 --> 00:03:59,640
Oh, right! Mamiya-kun.

64
00:04:00,060 --> 00:04:01,840
It's a good thing you're off tomorrow.

65
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:03,060
Where are we going next?

66
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:03,940
Huh?
Wait.

67
00:04:05,070 --> 00:04:06,710
It's already 11:00 PM.

68
00:04:07,690 --> 00:04:09,500
It's only 9:00 AM in New York.

69
00:04:10,290 --> 00:04:11,290
Touma's dad...

70
00:04:11,450 --> 00:04:12,450
We're in Tokyo.

71
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,760
What's with that way of calling me?

72
00:04:15,010 --> 00:04:16,430
You can just call me "Dad."

73
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:26,840
Mamiya-kun, your reactions are so funny.

74
00:04:28,990 --> 00:04:30,870
Um... do you really not mind at all?

75
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:31,940
Mind what?

76
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:33,320
Well...

77
00:04:33,370 --> 00:04:34,370
About me...

78
00:04:34,780 --> 00:04:35,900
and Touma... you know...

79
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:37,350
Hmm?

80
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,120
Were you hoping I'd say something?

81
00:04:40,130 --> 00:04:41,130
Ah.

82
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:41,810
Like, you wanted me to oppose it

83
00:04:41,810 --> 00:04:43,310
to make your love burn even brighter?

84
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:44,720
That's not what I meant.

85
00:04:45,980 --> 00:04:47,180
Then you might be disappointed.

86
00:04:49,050 --> 00:04:50,770
I already looked into you through Tenma.

87
00:04:50,890 --> 00:04:52,190
So I've known about you for a while.

88
00:04:52,990 --> 00:04:53,990
Wait, what?

89
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:58,510
I was just curious what kind of person would date
someone as cold as Touma.

90
00:05:00,590 --> 00:05:02,100
I'd actually like to ask you.

91
00:05:02,390 --> 00:05:03,590
What's so good about that kid?

92
00:05:03,890 --> 00:05:05,280
He's cold and boring.

93
00:05:06,290 --> 00:05:08,230
That's not true at all.

94
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:11,070
Touma is very capable.

95
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:12,810
He also works incredibly hard.

96
00:05:13,620 --> 00:05:17,010
He's calm and looks out for everyone around him.

97
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,880
He's someone I truly respect.

98
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:21,170
And right now, he's working hard for his dream.

99
00:05:21,170 --> 00:05:22,320
I think he's amazing.

100
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,120
His dream?

101
00:05:24,780 --> 00:05:26,080
What exactly is that kid's dream?

102
00:05:26,980 --> 00:05:29,640
To become the top makeup artist for ROMY Japan.

103
00:05:30,090 --> 00:05:32,800
That's why it's decided he's going to Paris in the spring.

104
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:37,720
How small-minded.

105
00:05:38,310 --> 00:05:38,930
Huh?

106
00:05:38,930 --> 00:05:40,950
Just Japan? He's selling himself short.

107
00:05:41,370 --> 00:05:43,550
If you're going to do it, aim for the world.

108
00:05:43,580 --> 00:05:44,960
He's got no guts.

109
00:05:46,230 --> 00:05:47,710
That's because... I...

110
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:50,400
He's waiting until spring for Paris?

111
00:05:51,030 --> 00:05:53,080
If he were serious, he wouldn't wait until spring.

112
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:54,240
He'd go right now.

113
00:05:55,370 --> 00:05:56,830
If you can't act immediately,

114
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:59,640
then your heart isn't really in it.

115
00:06:00,670 --> 00:06:02,530
Besides, how long does he plan to stay at ROMY?

116
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:04,890
If he joined our company's cosmetics division,

117
00:06:04,890 --> 00:06:06,710
everything would be so much easier.

118
00:06:08,130 --> 00:06:09,130
Oh, I know.

119
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:12,680
If he's only staying at ROMY for your sake,

120
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:15,140
then why don't you just quit and join us too?

121
00:06:15,140 --> 00:06:16,320
Isn't that a great idea?

122
00:06:18,220 --> 00:06:19,480
Please take that back.

123
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,390
Huh...?

124
00:06:21,430 --> 00:06:23,060
Please don't talk like that.

125
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:26,650
- Touma is...
- No, no, think about it.

126
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:29,000
The dream of someone with no drive

127
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,020
is always just within arm's reach, isn't it?

128
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:34,280
And as for "hard work,"

129
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:37,570
at his level, wouldn't it be the same
no matter where he goes?

130
00:06:44,550 --> 00:06:45,550
I'm so furious!

131
00:06:46,910 --> 00:06:47,660
What's wrong?

132
00:06:47,660 --> 00:06:48,750
Did something happen?

133
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:50,920
It's your dad!

134
00:06:50,990 --> 00:06:52,580
He completely looks down on you.

135
00:06:53,430 --> 00:06:54,650
He even talked about ROMY like that.

136
00:06:54,710 --> 00:06:56,440
Wait, hold on.

137
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:58,180
Let me get this straight.

138
00:06:58,590 --> 00:07:00,010
Did you meet with him again?

139
00:07:05,310 --> 00:07:07,880
I told you not to get involved with him.

140
00:07:09,070 --> 00:07:10,070
I'm sorry...

141
00:07:10,250 --> 00:07:10,860
But...

142
00:07:10,860 --> 00:07:14,640
His values and yours are like oil and water.

143
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,290
You shouldn't have anything to do with him.

144
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:18,570
It's just a waste of energy.

145
00:07:19,820 --> 00:07:21,030
I just thought it was a rare opportunity.

146
00:07:21,420 --> 00:07:23,180
I wanted to try talking to him more.

147
00:07:24,260 --> 00:07:27,530
But then he said you should quit ROMY,

148
00:07:28,210 --> 00:07:30,580
and that being a makeup artist is the same anywhere.

149
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:33,410
It makes me so mad!

150
00:07:34,310 --> 00:07:37,110
You work so hard here at ROMY.

151
00:07:39,310 --> 00:07:41,440
I know he's your father, but...

152
00:07:42,790 --> 00:07:45,030
What does he think other people's jobs are?

153
00:07:46,780 --> 00:07:48,080
He clearly knows nothing

154
00:07:48,330 --> 00:07:49,780
about all the effort you've put in.

155
00:07:51,770 --> 00:07:53,990
It pisses me off that he looks down on you.

156
00:07:58,510 --> 00:07:59,710
This is rare.

157
00:08:00,870 --> 00:08:02,630
I've never seen Natsume-san this angry.

158
00:08:03,570 --> 00:08:05,520
Well, it's infuriating!

159
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:09,480
Why are you being so calm about it?

160
00:08:10,170 --> 00:08:12,500
Because I already know what kind of man he is.

161
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,080
More importantly,

162
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:17,040
what makes me even angrier is that
you're getting angry for his sake.

163
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:18,630
What?

164
00:08:18,630 --> 00:08:21,140
Making Natsume-san angry is my job.

165
00:08:22,780 --> 00:08:25,660
It bothers me that someone else
made you feel this way.

166
00:08:27,890 --> 00:08:30,000
I'm the only one who should be able to push your buttons.

167
00:08:31,570 --> 00:08:32,880
What kind of logic is that?

168
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:35,390
Think about it.

169
00:08:36,180 --> 00:08:37,170
In the last few years,

170
00:08:37,170 --> 00:08:39,670
have you ever been this mad at anyone besides me?

171
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:46,200
I guess... not...

172
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:48,680
See?

173
00:08:54,170 --> 00:08:58,580
So, Natsume-san, calm down.

174
00:09:00,980 --> 00:09:02,080
But you...

175
00:09:03,730 --> 00:09:05,730
Stop thinking about that guy.

176
00:09:06,730 --> 00:09:08,400
Just think about me.

177
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:11,190
Only get angry at me.

178
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:17,430
Anyway, I'm off tomorrow.

179
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:19,980
Is there anything you want to do?

180
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,060
Anything is fine.

181
00:09:25,180 --> 00:09:26,180
Actually,

182
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:28,240
I'm a bit tired today.

183
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,000
I might just want to lounge around.

184
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:33,180
Okay.

185
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:35,910
What have you been smiling about?

186
00:09:37,430 --> 00:09:38,530
Well,

187
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:42,620
it's just that Natsume-san got so angry for my sake.

188
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:45,850
It makes me happy.

189
00:09:47,570 --> 00:09:49,960
It's not funny, you know.

190
00:09:53,490 --> 00:09:54,490
And besides...

191
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,610
All the hard work you do at ROMY...

192
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,880
I wish your dad could see even a little bit of it.

193
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:05,240
You're so kind.

194
00:10:06,970 --> 00:10:08,670
I'm serious.

195
00:10:12,210 --> 00:10:13,210
Okay.

196
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:38,400
(Incoming call: Tenma)

197
00:10:43,330 --> 00:10:44,530
Aren't you going to answer?

198
00:10:45,740 --> 00:10:46,940
It's Tenma.

199
00:10:47,170 --> 00:10:48,670
I don't want to see him on my day off.

200
00:10:57,220 --> 00:10:58,740
How does he even have my number...?

201
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:02,100
Hello? What do you want?

202
00:11:02,270 --> 00:11:03,720
Why do you have Natsume-san's number?

203
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:06,490
Ah, I see.

204
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:08,840
What's going on?

205
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,000
What did Tenma-san say?

206
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:12,900
Please.

207
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,200
Help me out.

208
00:11:14,670 --> 00:11:16,790
I need your help.

209
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:29,640
So?

210
00:11:29,950 --> 00:11:31,220
Explain yourself.

211
00:11:31,820 --> 00:11:33,050
Since you called us all the way out here,

212
00:11:33,050 --> 00:11:34,840
I assume it's something important.

213
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,720
Actually...

214
00:11:39,030 --> 00:11:41,970
Dad has another project going on besides the brand.

215
00:11:42,310 --> 00:11:45,030
But the partner company bailed today.

216
00:11:45,220 --> 00:11:46,590
We can't get a hold of them at all.

217
00:11:47,370 --> 00:11:49,010
And why are you coming to me?

218
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,920
It's a children's photography event.

219
00:11:54,020 --> 00:11:55,980
That guy is hosting a kids' event?

220
00:11:56,370 --> 00:11:57,370
Yes.
The kids get to pick out different outfits,

221
00:11:58,370 --> 00:11:59,730
get their hair and makeup done,

222
00:11:59,810 --> 00:12:01,920
and then a professional photographer takes their picture.

223
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:03,290
But...

224
00:12:04,060 --> 00:12:07,440
We can't find any replacement makeup artists.

225
00:12:08,330 --> 00:12:09,330
Huh?

226
00:12:09,660 --> 00:12:10,860
Touma and Mamiya-kun?

227
00:12:11,260 --> 00:12:12,260
What are you two doing here?

228
00:12:13,380 --> 00:12:14,380
Ah, Mamiya-kun.

229
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,030
Yesterday was so much fun.

230
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:19,240
We were called in to clean up your mess.

231
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:20,640
Ah, so that's what this is about.

232
00:12:21,070 --> 00:12:21,690
What?

233
00:12:21,690 --> 00:12:23,050
You're here to help?

234
00:12:23,050 --> 00:12:24,060
Thanks.

235
00:12:24,130 --> 00:12:25,430
Um... is this really going to be okay?

236
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,480
No, it's not okay at all.

237
00:12:31,130 --> 00:12:32,130
But...

238
00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:36,000
I only wanted to test the waters
with a children's charity event anyway.

239
00:12:36,050 --> 00:12:37,050
Forget it.

240
00:12:37,740 --> 00:12:39,110
Even though we already gave out the tickets...

241
00:12:39,330 --> 00:12:40,330
Let's just cancel it. Cancel.
Wait...

242
00:12:42,820 --> 00:12:45,310
You're canceling...?

243
00:12:46,710 --> 00:12:49,150
We already found a replacement photographer.

244
00:12:49,470 --> 00:12:51,270
We managed to sort out the costumes and staff too...

245
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:53,900
I don't see the point in forcing it if we might fail.

246
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:56,980
There's no point in doing a mediocre job.

247
00:12:58,910 --> 00:13:00,270
Please wait.

248
00:13:01,830 --> 00:13:04,350
So many people are already working
to make this happen, aren't they?

249
00:13:05,030 --> 00:13:07,200
And the kids must be so excited.

250
00:13:08,030 --> 00:13:09,030
How can you be so selfish...

251
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,710
Give it a rest.

252
00:13:14,250 --> 00:13:16,160
Stop deciding to give up on everything so easily.

253
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:17,180
You're jerking everyone around.

254
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:18,020
Don't you think it's time you stopped?

255
00:13:18,050 --> 00:13:20,140
You even dragged Natsume-san into this and made him mad.

256
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,860
Huh? I made him mad?

257
00:13:24,070 --> 00:13:25,060
Hmm?

258
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,440
Me?

259
00:13:27,180 --> 00:13:28,380
I made Mamiya-kun mad?

260
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,780
We just need makeup artists, right?

261
00:13:34,780 --> 00:13:35,780
Hmm?

262
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:44,860
Hey.

263
00:13:45,010 --> 00:13:46,300
The cavalry is here.

264
00:13:49,280 --> 00:13:50,480
Thank you guys so much.

265
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:51,600
No problem, it's nothing.

266
00:13:52,070 --> 00:13:54,520
Mamiya Natsume, who are these people...?

267
00:13:55,030 --> 00:13:57,200
Ah, they're makeup artists from ROMY.

268
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:59,530
They trained with Touma.

269
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:01,410
They came to help as soon as they got the message.

270
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:05,810
Long time no see, Sahashi-bro.

271
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:08,320
Wait... what?

272
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:09,670
Alright, leave it to us.

273
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,840
So, how are we splitting the work?

274
00:14:12,110 --> 00:14:14,250
- Nanjo-san and Yoshida-san, you're on makeup.
- Got it.

275
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:16,350
Manaka-san and Endo-san,
please handle the hair.

276
00:14:16,350 --> 00:14:17,560
- Okay.
- Understood.

277
00:14:18,850 --> 00:14:20,240
Natsume-san, you're with me.

278
00:14:20,970 --> 00:14:21,830
Okay.

279
00:14:21,940 --> 00:14:23,230
Tenma, what's the status?

280
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:24,380
Ah...

281
00:14:24,470 --> 00:14:27,040
The studio is ready and the costumes are all here.

282
00:14:29,170 --> 00:14:30,170
Touma.

283
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:31,530
What about me? What should I do?

284
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:34,000
- Just go over there and stay out of the way.
- Fine, fine.

285
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:50,910
What is it, Mamiya-kun?

286
00:14:51,740 --> 00:14:52,740
Well...

287
00:14:54,820 --> 00:14:56,400
I want you to watch closely.

288
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:58,020
Watch Touma.

289
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:03,320
Today's event is for kids
between six and ten years old.

290
00:15:04,050 --> 00:15:05,910
Please keep the makeup natural.

291
00:15:05,910 --> 00:15:06,850
- Okay.
- Understand.

292
00:15:07,170 --> 00:15:09,800
It might get busy, but I'm counting on you.

293
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:10,540
No problem.

294
00:15:12,450 --> 00:15:13,720
Hmm...

295
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:19,880
And then...

296
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:26,020
The children dressed up as their favorite princes and princesses.

297
00:15:27,780 --> 00:15:29,580
Amidst all the smiles,

298
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:32,510
the photography event was a huge success.

299
00:15:34,460 --> 00:15:36,360
Mister, today was so much fun!

300
00:15:36,450 --> 00:15:38,090
Thank you! Bye-bye!

301
00:15:38,260 --> 00:15:40,370
Thank you, see you next time.

302
00:15:40,370 --> 00:15:42,320
- See you!
- Bye!

303
00:15:44,870 --> 00:15:45,880
Bye-bye!

304
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:47,120
Bye.

305
00:15:48,290 --> 00:15:49,790
- That was so fun.
- I had a great time.

306
00:16:01,970 --> 00:16:07,390
Touma, and everyone, thank you so much.

307
00:16:07,950 --> 00:16:10,000
Thanks to you all, the event was a success.

308
00:16:11,230 --> 00:16:13,880
- Sahashi asked, so how could we say no?
- Exactly.

309
00:16:14,710 --> 00:16:17,370
Sahashi-kun's leadership is as good as they say.

310
00:16:17,780 --> 00:16:19,740
It was really impressive.

311
00:16:19,950 --> 00:16:23,430
I'm still no match for Chief Mamiya,
who handles the busy counters on weekends.

312
00:16:24,740 --> 00:16:26,150
Alright, good work everyone.

313
00:16:26,810 --> 00:16:28,290
Let's go celebrate!

314
00:16:28,420 --> 00:16:30,790
- Let's go.
- Thank you so much.

315
00:16:30,970 --> 00:16:32,020
Alright, we're heading out.

316
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:33,720
Thanks, everyone.

317
00:16:33,930 --> 00:16:35,200
- You were a huge help.
- Good work.

318
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,280
- Yeah, good work.
- Hey, stop touching my butt!

319
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:39,750
Good work, everyone.

320
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:41,830
By the way, Touma, I'm impressed.

321
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,360
I didn't know you were so good at leading an event like this.

322
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:46,840
Um...

323
00:16:49,110 --> 00:16:51,500
Please take back what you said yesterday.

324
00:16:55,380 --> 00:16:56,480
What happened here today,

325
00:16:56,670 --> 00:16:58,500
the fact that everyone from ROMY rushed to help,

326
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:02,660
is proof of all the hard work he's put in until now.

327
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:06,800
So,

328
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:10,790
even if your standards for success are different,

329
00:17:12,530 --> 00:17:15,240
please don't trample on Touma's dedication.

330
00:17:19,470 --> 00:17:20,790
As for Touma...

331
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:23,590
I've watched him more closely than anyone else.

332
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:27,860
I think he's the coolest person in the world.

333
00:17:33,110 --> 00:17:35,830
So I can't ignore anyone who speaks lightly of him.

334
00:17:38,010 --> 00:17:39,210
Even if it's family.

335
00:17:50,580 --> 00:17:51,580
Touma...

336
00:17:55,630 --> 00:17:57,300
You've found yourself a great partner.

337
00:17:59,010 --> 00:18:00,010
Huh?

338
00:18:00,630 --> 00:18:02,470
Ah, no, I mean...

339
00:18:03,410 --> 00:18:04,680
So that's how it is.

340
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:07,180
Until you fix that cynical personality of yours,

341
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:09,870
please don't show your face to Natsume-san.

342
00:18:10,070 --> 00:18:11,070
Ever again.

343
00:18:11,140 --> 00:18:13,620
Wow, how cold.

344
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,200
But well...

345
00:18:17,310 --> 00:18:19,750
I think I get what Mamiya-kun is trying to say.

346
00:18:20,030 --> 00:18:21,130
I take back what I said.

347
00:18:23,090 --> 00:18:24,030
But Touma...

348
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:26,040
You...

349
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:29,530
I thought you were just a quiet,
cold, and boring guy.

350
00:18:31,060 --> 00:18:34,120
- Turns out you're actually pretty capable.
- Well, obviously.

351
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:35,600
I...

352
00:18:35,710 --> 00:18:37,880
I'm much more grounded than you are.

353
00:18:41,010 --> 00:18:42,010
Natsume-san.

354
00:18:42,050 --> 00:18:43,420
Let's go clean up the rest.

355
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:46,550
Good idea.

356
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:51,300
Some time passed after that.

357
00:18:51,990 --> 00:18:54,900
The ROMY and Whimsical collaboration was a success.

358
00:18:55,930 --> 00:18:57,940
It ended on a high note with a great turnout.

359
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:01,380
Touma's father and Tenma-san

360
00:19:01,380 --> 00:19:04,910
are heading back to New York tomorrow.

361
00:19:05,770 --> 00:19:07,360
He's so small.

362
00:19:07,990 --> 00:19:10,180
So cute...

363
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:12,900
Is this Touma?

364
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:14,860
He's adorable.

365
00:19:15,610 --> 00:19:16,610
Right?

366
00:19:18,170 --> 00:19:19,710
Do we have to look at all of these?

367
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:21,090
Yeah, why not?

368
00:19:21,980 --> 00:19:23,410
It's not that I mind, but...

369
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:25,600
Maybe we should take them home to look at...

370
00:19:25,890 --> 00:19:27,540
Oh, which one, which one?

371
00:19:27,790 --> 00:19:29,480
Please don't get so close.

372
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:32,170
Oh.

373
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:35,520
So Touma had a phase like this too.

374
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:37,790
I don't remember it at all, though.

375
00:19:39,350 --> 00:19:40,450
If Mei were here,

376
00:19:40,550 --> 00:19:42,250
we'd probably have even more to talk about.

377
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:44,220
Mei?

378
00:19:44,330 --> 00:19:46,330
Yeah, my beloved wife.

379
00:19:47,910 --> 00:19:50,790
She couldn't make it to Japan this time because of a client project.

380
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:57,090
I've actually been thinking lately.

381
00:19:58,340 --> 00:19:59,850
If I hadn't gone to New York back then,

382
00:20:00,570 --> 00:20:02,890
and had lived a life as an ordinary dad in Japan...

383
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:06,050
Like, playing with my kids and all that.

384
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:09,000
I wonder what that would have been like.

385
00:20:10,950 --> 00:20:13,740
That children's photography event...

386
00:20:15,630 --> 00:20:17,090
Could it be...?

387
00:20:19,460 --> 00:20:21,720
Well, it's too late for that now.

388
00:20:26,820 --> 00:20:29,240
I seem to be thoroughly hated by you anyway.

389
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,010
But I'm glad I got to meet you.

390
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:32,200
Mamiya Natsume-kun.

391
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:36,300
Um,

392
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:38,870
it's not that I hate you.

393
00:20:39,170 --> 00:20:39,980
Huh?

394
00:20:40,870 --> 00:20:41,870
It's just...

395
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:45,740
No matter who it is,

396
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:49,640
I don't like it when Touma is dismissed so easily.

397
00:20:50,850 --> 00:20:52,550
When that happens, I'll stand up for him.

398
00:20:52,670 --> 00:20:53,770
I'll protect him.

399
00:20:56,150 --> 00:20:57,150
I...

400
00:20:58,460 --> 00:21:00,270
I'm always on his side.

401
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,810
I'm committed to that.

402
00:21:03,340 --> 00:21:04,540
And for that reason...

403
00:21:06,210 --> 00:21:07,530
I'll talk back to you if I have to.

404
00:21:07,530 --> 00:21:08,330
That's all it is.

405
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:14,850
Natsume-san...

406
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:22,850
Tenma-san?

407
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:26,060
No, sorry.

408
00:21:26,270 --> 00:21:27,520
Mamiya Natsume.

409
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:32,550
Looking at this scene,

410
00:21:34,190 --> 00:21:35,290
it's almost like...

411
00:21:36,210 --> 00:21:38,540
we're having a family party.

412
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,150
Can I take a picture?

413
00:21:44,850 --> 00:21:45,960
Sure, sure, go ahead.

414
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:48,600
I'm taking it now.

415
00:21:48,620 --> 00:21:50,180
Come on, smile.

416
00:21:52,010 --> 00:21:53,010
I'll join in too.

417
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:56,360
Alright, smile!

418
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:58,900
Did you get it?

419
00:22:01,930 --> 00:22:03,950
I'm going to show this to Mom.

420
00:22:05,410 --> 00:22:07,380
- Let's go, Natsume-san!
- Huh?

421
00:22:07,410 --> 00:22:09,680
Hey, you're welcome back anytime.

422
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:12,090
We can have another good argument then.

423
00:22:12,330 --> 00:22:13,810
I'm not letting you see him again.

424
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:17,250
Please don't approach Natsume-san anymore.

425
00:22:17,670 --> 00:22:18,930
I won't even let you argue with him.

426
00:22:20,870 --> 00:22:22,290
So, Natsume-san,

427
00:22:22,990 --> 00:22:24,980
you don't have to try so hard to stand up for me anymore.

428
00:22:26,010 --> 00:22:28,670
If there's anything else I need help with,

429
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:30,010
I'll just ask you then.

430
00:22:30,810 --> 00:22:32,050
You can count on me.

431
00:22:32,820 --> 00:22:33,820
Hey.

432
00:22:34,670 --> 00:22:37,780
Even so, the way you treat Mamiya-kun
versus me is way too different!

433
00:22:37,870 --> 00:22:38,670
Huh?

434
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:40,360
What's with that doting look on your face?

435
00:22:40,910 --> 00:22:41,910
We're leaving now.

436
00:22:41,950 --> 00:22:43,610
I can't stand being interrupted anymore.

437
00:22:47,030 --> 00:22:49,390
Even if he tries to act all cool...

438
00:22:49,770 --> 00:22:51,900
What are you doing?

439
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:53,180
Hey, look, Dad.

440
00:22:53,220 --> 00:22:54,220
Hmm?

441
00:22:57,150 --> 00:22:58,150
Tenma-san.

442
00:22:58,230 --> 00:22:59,760
He seems really happy.

443
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:01,680
About what?

444
00:23:01,970 --> 00:23:02,970
Hmm?

445
00:23:03,610 --> 00:23:05,590
He said before that even just once in his life,

446
00:23:05,590 --> 00:23:07,310
he wanted to have a family party.

447
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:09,170
That's why he took the photo.

448
00:23:09,310 --> 00:23:11,600
If we're taking photos,
I'd rather it just be the two of us.

449
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:13,140
Huh?

450
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:17,290
Let's take a bunch while we can.

451
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:19,840
You're hopeless.

452
00:23:22,490 --> 00:23:23,680
The view over there is better.

453
00:23:24,210 --> 00:23:25,210
Yeah.

454
00:23:46,610 --> 00:23:47,860
I think that's enough.

455
00:23:48,730 --> 00:23:50,700
I feel like I've taken a lifetime's worth of photos.

456
00:23:51,220 --> 00:23:53,020
No, it's not nearly enough.

457
00:23:53,740 --> 00:23:55,260
Because no photo can compare to the real thing.

458
00:24:00,540 --> 00:24:04,430
Well, at least...

459
00:24:05,450 --> 00:24:06,550
Here, take this.

460
00:24:16,780 --> 00:24:17,880
Can I open it?

461
00:24:18,050 --> 00:24:19,050
Yeah.

462
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,240
It's just like the one you gave me.

463
00:24:32,870 --> 00:24:34,220
I chose a matching one in black.

464
00:24:36,990 --> 00:24:38,310
You can wear it when you go to Paris.

465
00:24:41,740 --> 00:24:43,040
Thank you.

466
00:24:44,280 --> 00:24:45,510
I'm really happy.

467
00:24:46,310 --> 00:24:47,310
Natsume-san.

468
00:24:52,620 --> 00:24:53,620
Put it on for me.

469
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:55,420
- Huh? Right now?
- Yes.

470
00:24:56,780 --> 00:24:57,780
Okay.

471
00:24:59,180 --> 00:25:00,500
- This side?
- Yeah.

472
00:25:05,830 --> 00:25:06,910
Let's take a picture.

473
00:25:07,290 --> 00:25:09,030
- Another one?
- Mm-hmm.

474
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:16,280
After that,

475
00:25:17,300 --> 00:25:18,550
with the holiday collections,

476
00:25:19,260 --> 00:25:20,260
Christmas,

477
00:25:20,660 --> 00:25:21,660
and New Year's,

478
00:25:22,350 --> 00:25:24,030
time flew by.

479
00:25:25,420 --> 00:25:27,090
Before we knew it, it was February.

480
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:30,920
- I'll layer a bit more color for you.
- Okay.

481
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:37,610
The day Sahashi leaves for Paris

482
00:25:39,470 --> 00:25:41,280
is coming up next month.

483
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:48,250
(Next Episode)
The Twin Princes of Yurakucho.

484
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:49,750
We won't be seeing them for a while.

485
00:25:49,750 --> 00:25:51,390
So I have to take a good look.

486
00:25:51,530 --> 00:25:52,530
I'll be waiting for you.

487
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:55,040
Until you come back successful.

488
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:56,980
I'll be looking forward to it.
